            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes I agree - either the documentation should be updated or the behaviour should be changed.\n\n> [...] exactly [...]\n\nAgain, agree that this is misleading. I think the previous state (sometime in the distant past) was that you had to implement a `__richcmp__` method that has no direct Python equivalent, and the current implementation auto-constructs `__richcmp__` so it's mostly referring to that. I don't think we realised the inheritance behaviour was a bit odd.\n\n>  seems like having Cython check for `__hash__` or comparison methods on a subclass and then copy over any methods that should be inherited would suffice?\n\nThe complication is probably `cimport`ed/`extern` base classes where we don't have visibility on what's inherited. With that said, it probably isn't too difficult",
