        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "My data-free intuition is that the cases where users rely on the current behaviour (turn off equality/hashing if only hashing/equality is overridden) are more rare than the cases where users did/would get bitten by it.\n\nBut if we assume that the \"turn off\" use case is not entirely useless and that _some_ code might depend on it – what is a good way to disable eq/hash support for a subclass if the base class has it? Meaning, if we change the behaviour, how do we provide a way for our current users to migrate, preferably one that is backwards compatible itself?",
            "created_at": "2026-04-30T06:13:18Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7627#issuecomment-4350107178",
            "id": 4350107178,
